   343	
   344	From the standpoint of radiation theory, these SCB treatments of the
   345	ammonia maser differed from the Bloch magnetic resonance theory mainly
   346	in the fact that the field producing the stimulated emission was not
   347	\"externally applied\", but was the field previously radiated by the
   348	molecules themselves; in other words, radiation damping was now, due to
   349	the high Q of the cavity, an essential part of the theory, with the
   350	cavity Q appearing in the expressions for starting current, amplitude of
   351	oscillation, and frequency pulling factor. At this microwave frequency
   352	(24.8 GHz) ordinary (i.e., cavity-unassisted) spontaneous emission was
   353	still completely negligible, corresponding to radiative lifetimes of the
   354	order of months, while the cavity-assisted emission took place in less
   355	than a millisecond. It is true that the active sample now extended over
   356	many wavelengths, but one considered only its interaction with the
   357	$TM_{01}$ cavity mode, whose field is constant along the length of the
   358	beam, so that again it was the total moment of all the molecules that
   359	was considered the source of a classical electromagnetic field.
