   431	a continuum of field modes like those of free space. Because of this,
   432	and the magnitude of the Einstein
   433	A-coefficient ($\sim 10^8 \text{ sec}^{-1}$), spontaneous emission into
   434	modes other than the ones of interest is hardly ever negligible, and is
   435	often the dominant physical process at work. Finally, the optical cavity
   436	is of the order of a million wavelengths long, with the normal mode
   437	field reversing sign every half-wavelength along the cavity axis. This
